</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[189,1399,984,1045]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
A careful search of the relevant literature reveals no other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1848" box="[896,1035,984,1010]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Sertulariidae" genus="Sertularella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[896,1035,984,1010]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Sertularella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species which approaches the present hydroid in the morphology of its hydrothecae.
</paragraph>
